Ddoc

$(T h1,,DConf 2018$(BR) in Munich!)

$(P
The D Language Foundation is pleased to announce the international conference and hackathon DConf 2018 in Munich, Germany, May 2-5 2018.
)

$(P
DConf is the main face-to-face event for everyone in the D programming language community and anyone who wants to know what all the fuss is about. We are proud to be hosted in Munich, a hotbed of systems and embedded software with a strong and vibrant programmer community. And if you use the public transportation system, beware! The passenger information software is written in D by local company Funkwerk AG.
)

$(P
We are featuring growth and outreach as a special theme this year - if you have any friends who use another language who could benefit from learning more about the D language, let them know!
)

$(T h2,,Call for Submissions)

$(P
We are looking forward to your submission for a paper, talk, demo, panel, or research report for DConf 2018. All submissions should be directed to $(LINK2 mailto:foundation@dlang.org, foundation@dlang.org). The topics of choice are anything and everything related to the D language, such as:
)

$(UL

$(LI $(B Language techniques) enabled by the D language)

$(LI $(B Tools and techniques) for maximizing productivity when working in D)

$(LI $(B Experience reports) on using D in the real world)

$(LI $(B Under the hood) looks at compiler and standard library implementation artifacts)

$(LI $(B Hot topics) such as safe deterministic memory management, migrating from other languages, or community engagement)

$(LI $(B Research reports) by students doing research on or using the D language)

)

$(T h2,, Hackathon)

$(P
Building on the success of the past year's hackathon, we are happy to announce a day-long Hackathon on Saturday, May 5th. The day is largely unstructured, but we expect birds-of-a-feather groups to materialize naturally. Bring your laptop and your enthusiasm!
)

